All MEMs ran simulations without fishing, and three MEMs ran simulations with fishing for historical (1970–2005) and future (2006–2100) periods. Historical fishing reflected time-varying effort or mortality rates depending on MEM requirements, and future fishing was kept constant at 2005 levels (
 
  SI Appendix, 
  SI Methods
 ). Not all MEMs performed all simulations, and sensitivity analyses cross-checked subsets of results (
 
  SI Appendix, Table S3
 ).
